parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: False Activation of Automatic Emergency Braking System
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The false activation of the automatic emergency braking system can cause the vehicle to suddenly stop, leading to potential accidents or rear-end collisions, especially if there are vehicles behind.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly stops or brakes without any obstacles or hazards in front
the collision warning sounds
the brake warning appears on the dashboard
the vehicle comes to an abrupt stop
and the driver may be jolted forward.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the radar sensor can cause the automatic emergency braking system to malfunction, leading to false activations or failures to detect obstacles, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The radar sensor fails to detect obstacles
the collision warning sounds or fails to sound
the automatic emergency braking system malfunctions
and warning lights appear on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Software Issues with Automatic Emergency Braking System
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Software issues with the automatic emergency braking system can cause the system to malfunction, leading to false activations or failures to detect obstacles, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The automatic emergency braking system malfunctions
the collision warning sounds or fails to sound
the vehicle suddenly stops or brakes without any obstacles or hazards in front
and warning lights appear on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: False Activation of Automatic Emergency Braking System
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The false activation of the automatic emergency braking system can cause the vehicle to suddenly stop or slow down without warning, increasing the risk of rear-end collisions or accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly stops or slows down without warning
the ABS warning light illuminates
the brakes lock up
the vehicle stalls
a "Brake!" alert appears on the display screen
followed by beeps.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The melting of the visor hinge can cause the visor to hang down, obstructing the driver's and passenger's visibility, and potentially leading to accidents or injuries in the event of sudden stops or accidents.
symptoms: The visor hangs down to eye level
does not hold up
and blocks forward visibility.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Unnecessary Forward Collision Warning and Auto Brake Activation
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unnecessary activation of the forward collision warning and auto brake can cause sudden and unexpected stops, leading to accidents or injuries to the driver and passengers.
symptoms: The forward collision warning activates unexpectedly
followed by a hard brake
causing the driver and passengers to lurch forward.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The excessive paint chipping and flaking can lead to rust and corrosion, compromising the vehicle's structural integrity and affecting its overall appearance.
symptoms: Paint chips easily
exposing bare metal
especially on the doors
hood
and bumper.
